 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Oct. 22: Indian Rayon amp; Industries would seek shareholders? nod for amalgamation of Indo Gulf Fertilisers and Birla Global Finance with itself. The company?s board had approved the merger on September 11 to infuse investments in high-growth businesses. The shareholders? meeting will be held on November 16, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 New Delhi, Oct. 22: Ashok Leyland today reported a 74.2 per cent rise in net profit for the quarter ended September 30 at Rs 75 crore against Rs 43 crore in the same period last year. The company has clocked a 37.6 per cent rise in turnover to Rs 1,441 crore from Rs 1,047 crore in the same period last year. Net profit in the first six months stood at Rs 139.3 crore and turnover at Rs 2,673.9 crore.

 Mumbai, Oct. 22: Essel Propack today reported a 32.67 per cent rise in net profit of Rs 13.4 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 10.1 crore in the year-ago period.




